{
  "texts": [
    "6, 7 Rapidly evolving advances in LLMs-especially reasoning models-may lower the skill level required to use these tools by helping with tool selection, tuition and troubleshooting, and by providing easy-to-use interfaces.",
    "The tacit knowledge required to successfully carry out an attack has historically served as a barrier to biological weapon development.",
    "However, it has been hypothesised that certain AI developments may overcome this hurdle.",
    "8 Alongside these developments, the continued progress in AI agents and their ability to effectively design, build and use tools may blur the boundaries between different types of AI tools and models.",
    "It is essential that developers, funders and governments work together to address risks and responsibly govern these tools."
  ]
}